ng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Aldegunda di Saluzzo was born in 1124, in Milano, Milan, Lombardy, Italy as the daughter of Anselmo Di Saluzzo. She married Ottone Grande Visconti II in 1141, in Milano, Milan, Lombardy, Italy. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1153, in her hometown, at the age of 29."},"et":{"1124–1153":"1124–1153","1143–1170":"1143–1170","1159–Female":"1159–Surnud","–1213":"–1213","–Male":"Surnud","1159":"1159","1213":"1213","1124":"1124","1143":"1143","1153":"1153","1141":"1141","1170":"1170","Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italy":"Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Itaalia"},"fi":{"1124–1153":"1124–1153","1143–1170":"1143–1170","1159–Female":"1159–Kuollut","–1213":"–1213","–Male":"Kuollut","1159":"1159","1213":"1213","1124":"1124","1143":"1143","1153":"1153","1141":"1141","1170":"1170","Milan, Milano, Lombardia, Italy":"Milano, Milano, Lombardia, Italia"},"fr":{"1124–1153":"1124–1153","1143–1170":"1143–1170","1159–Female":"1